Meet the Connected Capability Networks - Online Event

17 September 2025 17 September 2025

Satellite Applications Catapult Online

Established by the Satellite Applications Catapult in 2023, the Connected Capability Networks (CCNs) are tackling a key challenge for the UK space sector: fragmentation of expertise, infrastructure, and knowledge across different localities and industries.

By bringing together stakeholders from industry, academia, and government, the CCNs connect communities, strengthen collaboration, and highlight how space data and technologies can deliver solutions to national priorities.

Join us at our Meet the Connected Capability Networks - Online Event on 17th September. Each CCN will share updates from the last six months, plans for the next six, and there will be an opportunity to ask questions.
